00033  * Summary:
00034  *
00035  *  Function        Parameter Type   Parameters     Description
00036  *
00037  *  SR                                              Set Dominant Bistable
00038  *                  S1  BOOL         Input          Sets the output Q1.
00039  *                  R   BOOL         Input          Resets the output Q1.
00040  *                  Q1  BOOL         Output         The output value.
00041  *
00042  *  RS                                              Reset Dominant Bistable
00043  *                  S   BOOL         Input          Sets the output Q1.
00044  *                  R1  BOOL         Input          Resets the output Q1.
00045  *                  Q1  BOOL         Output         The output value.
00046  *
00047  *  R_TRIG                                          Rising Edge Detector
00048  *                  CLK BOOL         Input          A rising edge sets the output Q for one execution.
00049  *                  Q   BOOL         Output         The output value.
00050  *
00051  *  F_TRIG                                          Falling Edge Detector
00052  *                  CLK BOOL         Input          A falling edge sets the output Q for one execution.
00053  *                  Q   BOOL         Output         The output value.
00054  *
00055  *  CTU                                             Counts up from zero to a preset value.
00056  *                  CU  BOOL         R_EDGE Input   A rising edge increments the counter value CV by 1.
00057  *                  R   BOOL         Input          Resets the output Q and the counter value CV.
00058  *                  PV  INT          Input          The counter limit value.
00059  *                  Q   BOOL         Output         Set to true when the counter value CV reaches PV.
00060  *                  CV  INT          Input          The current counter value.
00061  *
00062  *  CTD                                             Counts down from a preset value to zero.
00063  *                  CD  BOOL         R_EDGE Input   A rising edge decrements the counter value CV by 1.
00064  *                  LD  BOOL         Input          Resets the output Q and the counter value CV.
00065  *                  PV  INT          Input          The counter limit value.
00066  *                  Q   BOOL         Output         Set to true when the counter value CV reaches PV.
00067  *                  CV  INT          Input          The current counter value.
00068  *
00069  *  TP                                              Generate a fixed duration pulse.
00070  *                  IN  BOOL         Input          A rising edge starts the fixed duration pulse.
00071  *                  PT  TIME         Input          The duration of the pulse.
00072  *                  Q   BOOL         Output         Set to true during the pulse.
00073  *                  ET  TIME         Output         The elapsed time of the pulse.
00074  *
00075  *  TON                                             Turn an output on after a delay.
00076  *                  IN  BOOL         Input          A rising edge starts the timer.
00077  *                  PT  TIME         Input          The duration of timer.
00078  *                  Q   BOOL         Output         Set to true after delay PT.
00079  *                  ET  TIME         Output         The elapsed time of the timer.
00080  *
00081  *  TOF                                             Turn an output off after a delay.
00082  *                  IN  BOOL         Input          A rising edge starts the timer.
00083  *                  PT  TIME         Input          The duration of timer.
00084  *                  Q   BOOL         Output         Set to false after delay PT.
00085  *                  ET  TIME         Output         The elapsed time of the timer.
00086  */
